{
  "texts": [
    "The two sublayers are connected by a residual connection [60], followed by layer normalization [4].The output of each sublayer is LayerNorm (x + Sublayer(x)), where Sublayer(x) is the function implemented by the sublayer itself.",
    "To facilitate these residual connections, all sublayers in the model, as well as the embedding layers, produce outpus of dimension d model = 5122.",
    "[67] Decoder: Inserts a third sublayer, which performs multi-head attention over the output of the encoder stack.",
    "We also modify the self-attention sublayer in the decoder stack to prevent positions from attending to subsequent positions.The most common Transformer architecture is the Bidirectional Encoder Representation from Transformers (BERT) [19].",
    "BERT improves upon the unidirectional by using a MLM pre-training objective inspired by Cloze tasks [65]."
  ]
}